          "text": "Adjacency matrix"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "Degree matrix"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "Adjacency matrix",
      "explanation": "Warshall's algorithm operates on the adjacency matrix to compute the transitive closure.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-6",
      "question": "What does the entry M[i][j] = 1 indicate in Warshall's algorithm's result?",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "Distance from i to j is 1"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "There is no path from i to j"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "There exists a path from i to j"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "Weight of edge i to j"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "There exists a path from i to j",
      "explanation": "In transitive closure, 1 indicates reachability (a path exists), while 0 indicates no path.",
      "difficulty": "easy"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-7",
      "question": "Floyd's algorithm can handle graphs with:",
      "options": [
        {
          "key": "A",
