      "correctAnswer": "Vertices, vertices, and intermediate vertices",
      "explanation": "The standard Floyd's algorithm has loops: for k in vertices, for i in vertices, for j in vertices.",
      "difficulty": "medium"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-9",
      "question": "In Warshall's algorithm, the update formula R[i][j] = R[i][j] OR (R[i][k] AND R[k][j]) uses:",
