        {
          "key": "A",
          "text": "Arithmetic operations"
        },
        {
          "key": "B",
          "text": "Logical/boolean operations"
        },
        {
          "key": "C",
          "text": "String operations"
        },
        {
          "key": "D",
          "text": "Bitwise operations only"
        }
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "Logical/boolean operations",
      "explanation": "Warshall's uses boolean algebra: OR for path existence, AND for path through intermediate vertex.",
      "difficulty": "medium"
    },
    {
      "id": "mcq-10",
      "question": "What is the space complexity of both algorithms?",
